Sentencas: In this work, a deep learning accelerated homogenization framework is developed for prediction of elastic modulus of porous materials directly from their inner microstructures.
Titulo: Predicting elastic modulus of porous La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes from microstructures via FEM and deep learning

Sentencas: The finite element method (FEM) and the homogenization theory are used to obtain the macroscopic properties of materials based on their microstructures.
Titulo: Predicting elastic modulus of porous La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes from microstructures via FEM and deep learning

Sentencas: Based on a large dataset consisting of various microstructures and corresponding elastic properties via FEM, a deep convolutional neural network (CNN) is trained to capture the nonlinear functional relationship between the microstructure features and their macroscopic elastic properties.
Titulo: Predicting elastic modulus of porous La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes from microstructures via FEM and deep learning

Sentencas: The deep learning model is finally well validated against extra new samples with excellent predictive performances.
Titulo: Predicting elastic modulus of porous La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes from microstructures via FEM and deep learning

Sentencas: This demonstrates that the CNN deep learning model can be trusted as a surrogate model for the FEM based homogenization method, with the computation time being reduced by several orders of magnitude.
Titulo: Predicting elastic modulus of porous La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes from microstructures via FEM and deep learning

Sentencas: The proposed deep learning framework is highly extendable for prediction of various macroscopic properties from microstructures.
Titulo: Predicting elastic modulus of porous La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes from microstructures via FEM and deep learning
